commits.message:
Added deltaFiles2 as a faster implementation of deltaFiles

deltaFiles2() uses diffTrees() instead of parseTree() that make it 5-6 times faster and more effective in memory consumption. However, there may be some more ways to improve it further. It should replace deltaFiles() after an additional testing of effectiveness.
Add typed views for buffers to simplify indexing
Fix loose partial object header reading in some cases
Remove caching of trees since it leads to heap overflow for huge repos
Fix constructing paths in some case on deltaFiles()
Use second parameter in readObjectByOid/Hash to disabling caching
Fix crash when `packed-refs` doesn't exist and some path related fixes
Fix int32 overflow on reading of encoded offset
Fix parsing a multiline value and gpgsig in commit & annotated tag headers
Refactoring of pack files, initial pack-*.rev support
Increase header buffer size to avoid some additional reads
Use a faster solution for inflate, reduces memory consumption as well
Boost commit & tag content parsing performance
